lead_paragraph: CUBA.--INTERFERENCE OF FRANCE AND ENGLAND.--The Washington Republic of yesterday states that there is reason to believe that France and England have agreed to render aid to Spain to retain its hold on Cuba, subject to certain provisions, and requiring Spain to remove the principal grievances of which the Cubans complain.
